Google Analytics 4 Connection

Create a remote connection using the Google Analytics 4 connector to sync Google Analytics data to CRM Analytics.

To validate your settings and attempt to connect to the source, click Save & Test. If the connection fails, CRM Analytics shows possible reasons.

Use a Google service account instead of a user account to grant access to your Google Analytics data.

Generate a JSON file containing the required client email and private key from the IAM & Admin page in the Google Cloud Platform Console.

All settings require a value, unless otherwise indicated.

Connection Name
Developer Name
Description
Client Email
Private Key

Enter the private_key value from the JSON file.

Advanced Object Properties

StartDate
EndDate
PropertyID
The Property ID for the Google Analytics account, which determines which data is available for sync.

Keep these considerations in mind when working with the Google Analytics 4 connector:

A connected object name must start with a letter and can contain only letters, digits, or underscores.
This connector can sync up to 10 million rows or 5 GB per object, whichever limit it reaches first.
Custom fields arenâ€™t supported.
Google Analytics stores your website data as a binary large object (blob).
Knowledge of Google Analytics Data API is necessary when selecting which virtual objects to connect to.
